  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Slice the <strong>red cabbage</strong> into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> large wedges, keeping the stalks intact so they stay together, trimming away any browned edges</p><p>Top, tail and grate the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> wedges</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-cabbage-wedges-with-nutty-pesto-rice/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>red cabbage wedges</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and sprinkle with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 25-30 min or until the stalks of the cabbage are fork-tender – these are your <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>red cabbage wedges</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-cabbage-wedges-with-nutty-pesto-rice/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the cabbage is cooking, add the <strong>white long grain rice</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and 400ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 16-18 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is almost cooked with a slight bite (you'll finish cooking it in step 6!)</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and keep covered</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-cabbage-wedges-with-nutty-pesto-rice/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pine nuts</strong>, <strong>blanched almonds</strong> and <strong>hazelnuts</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden – these are your <strong>toasted nuts</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-cabbage-wedges-with-nutty-pesto-rice/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and discard the stems</p><p>Once the nuts are toasted, add <strong>half</strong> to a <strong>food processor </strong>(save the rest for garnish and reserve the pan!)</p><p>Add the <strong>mint leaves </strong>with the <strong>basil</strong> and the juice of 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> <strong>lemon wedges</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> cold water</strong> and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>salt </strong>and pulse until roughly blitzed – this is your <strong>nutty pesto</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-cabbage-wedges-with-nutty-pesto-rice/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>grated courgette</strong> and <strong>sliced garlic</strong> with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong>, then cook for 2 min until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> cooked rice </strong>and cook for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-cabbage-wedges-with-nutty-pesto-rice/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once everything is combined, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>nutty pesto</strong> (save the rest for later!) to the pan and mix it all together – this is your <strong>nutty pesto rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-red-cabbage-wedges-with-nutty-pesto-rice/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> roasted red cabbage wedges</strong> over the <strong>nutty pesto rice</strong></p><p>Drizzle with the <strong>remaining nutty pesto</strong> and garnish with the <strong>lemon wedges </strong>and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>toasted nuts</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
